        step1PrayerTitle:'Opening prayer',
        step1Prayer:'Come, Holy Spirit. Give me light to see myself as You see me, honesty not to justify myself, humility to acknowledge my sin, and trust to return to the Father. May this examination be neither superficial nor hard of heart, but clean, sober, and true. Amen.',
        step1PrayerSub:'Interior penance begins not from the outside, but from the conversion of the heart <strong>(CCC 1430)</strong>.',
        step1TermsTitle:'Pastoral use notice',
        step1Term1:'<strong>1. Preparation tool, not a sacrament.</strong> This guide is an aid for preparing for sacramental confession. It does not replace the Sacrament of Reconciliation, spiritual direction, or the judgment of the confessor. Only a priest can give absolution.',
        step1Term2:'<strong>2. Doctrinal content.</strong> The content is based on official sources of the Catholic Church — the Catechism, the Compendium, and Magisterial documents. Even so, it may contain inaccuracies or be outdated. For any serious doctrinal question, consult a priest.',
        step1Term3:'<strong>3. For adults.</strong> This guide contains questions on moral topics that require maturity to understand well — including sexuality, relationships, and substance use. It is not intended for minors without the accompaniment of a responsible adult.',
        step1Term4:'<strong>4. Scrupulosity and religious anxiety.</strong> If you tend toward scrupulosity, religious anxiety, or persistent doubts of conscience, use this tool calmly and always under the guidance of a stable priest. Do not use it to re-examine sins already confessed.',
        step1Term5:'<strong>5. Privacy and data.</strong> Everything you mark is stored only in local storage on this device. It is not sent to any external server or accessible by the Community. If you share the device, consider clearing the session when finished using the "Clear all" button.',
        step1Term6:'<strong>6. No guarantee of completeness.</strong> The examination covers the most common areas of moral life, but is not exhaustive. There may be particular situations in your life not covered here. The confessor helps discern what the examination cannot reach.',
        step1Term7:'<strong>7. Proper use.</strong> This tool is intended to be used once per confession period as a focused preparation. It is not designed for daily use or repeated examination of sins already confessed.',
        step1AcceptLabel:'I have read this notice and understand that this guide is a pastoral aid to help me prepare well for confession, not a substitute for the sacrament.',
