        resAntesKicker:'Resource', resAntesTitle:'Before you begin',
        resAntesSub:'You are not entering a space of condemnation, but an encounter with God, who loves you, awaits you, and wants to heal your heart.',
        resAntesAcc1Title:'What is an examination of conscience?',
        resAntesAcc1Body:'It is a moment of prayer in which you review your thoughts, words, actions, and omissions before God. It helps you recognize your sins honestly, awaken repentance, and prepare for a good confession.',
        resAntesAcc2Title:'How to dispose yourself interiorly',
        resAntesAcc2Body:'Find a moment of silence. Make the sign of the cross and ask for the light of the Holy Spirit. It is not just about remembering things, but about letting God show you truthfully what needs to be healed.',
        resAntesAcc3Title:'Opening prayer',
        resAntesAcc3Prayer:'Come, Holy Spirit. Illuminate my mind, move my heart, and help me to see myself as You see me. Give me sincerity to acknowledge my sins, humility to confess them, and trust to abandon myself to God\'s mercy. Amen.',
        resAntesAcc4Title:'Keys for a good examination',
        resAntesAcc4Body:'<ul><li>Stand before God, not just before yourself.</li><li>Look at your life truthfully, without excuses.</li><li>Remember also the things you failed to do.</li><li>Do not get lost in unnecessary details.</li><li>Let yourself be guided by the Word of God.</li></ul>',
        resAntesAcc5Title:'Attitudes of the heart',
        resAntesAcc5Body:'Make your examination with: <strong>humility</strong> to acknowledge the truth; <strong>faith</strong> to believe in forgiveness; <strong>hope</strong> not to be discouraged; <strong>trust</strong> to return to God; <strong>sincere desire</strong> to change.',
        resAntesAcc6Title:'If it has been a long time since your last confession',
        resAntesAcc6Body:'Do not be afraid. What matters is not how long it has been, but that today you are taking the step of returning to God.',
        resComoKicker:'Resource', resComoTitle:'How to confess',
        resComoSub:'You do not need to speak perfectly. You need to come with humility, clarity, and truth.',
        resComoS1Title:'Begin with recollection', resComoS1Desc:'Make the sign of the cross and begin with peace.',
        resComoS2Title:'Say how much time has passed', resComoS2Example:'"Father, it has been several months since my last confession."',
        resComoS3Title:'Confess your sins clearly', resComoS3Desc:'State your sins concretely, simply, and humbly. Call things by their name and avoid justifying yourself.',
        resComoS4Title:'Listen to the priest', resComoS4Desc:'He may guide you or ask a question. Listen to him with openness.',
        resComoS5Title:'Make your act of contrition', resComoS5Prayer:'My Lord Jesus Christ, I am heartily sorry for having offended You. I firmly resolve, with Your grace, to sin no more and to avoid the occasions of sin. Amen.',
        resComoS6Title:'Receive absolution', resComoS6Desc:'Christ himself forgives you through the priest. Receive it with faith and gratitude.',
        resComoS7Title:'Complete your penance', resComoS7Desc:'It is not a punishment, but a concrete help. Do it promptly and with devotion.',
        resComoCallout:'A good confession is not the longest one, but the most sincere.',
        resDespuesKicker:'Resource', resDespuesTitle:'After confession',
        resDespuesSub:'You have received an immense gift: God\'s forgiveness. The Lord has reconciled you to himself and calls you to walk in his grace.',
        resDespuesAcc1Title:'Give thanks to God',
        resDespuesAcc1Body:'Stay a few minutes in prayer. Give thanks for the forgiveness received and rest in God\'s mercy.',
        resDespuesAcc1Prayer:'Thank you, Lord, for having forgiven me. Thank you for not tiring of me. Thank you for lifting me up, cleansing me, and giving me peace. Help me to live as your child and to walk in faithfulness. Amen.',
        resDespuesAcc2Title:'Complete your penance', resDespuesAcc2Body:'Complete your penance as soon as possible, if you can right then and there. It is a concrete response to the love you have received.',
        resDespuesAcc3Title:'Preserve your peace', resDespuesAcc3Body:'Do not go back to carrying what God has already forgiven. If you have confessed well, trust in the mercy you have received.',
        resDespuesAcc4Title:'Make a concrete resolution', resDespuesAcc4Body:'Confession also moves you to change. Ask yourself: <strong>What do I need to correct? What occasion of sin must I avoid? What concrete step will I take starting today?</strong>',
        resDespuesAcc5Title:'Persevere', resDespuesAcc5Body:'Return to prayer. Feed on the Word of God. Participate in the Eucharist. Do not give up if you are still struggling. <strong>God works in long processes too.</strong>',
        resFaqKicker:'Resource', resFaqTitle:'Frequently asked questions', resFaqSub:'Clear answers to help you live this sacrament better.',
        resFaqQ1:'What if it has been a long time since my last confession?', resFaqA1:'Come back without fear. What matters is not how long it has been, but that today you are taking the step of returning to God.',
        resFaqQ2:'What if I feel ashamed?', resFaqA2:'That is normal. But do not let shame keep you from forgiveness. The priest is there to help you, not to humiliate you.',
        resFaqQ3:'What if I do not know what to say?', resFaqA3:'You can begin like this: <em>"Father, I need help with my confession."</em>',
        resFaqQ4:'Do I have to say all my sins?', resFaqA4:'You must sincerely confess all grave sins you are aware of. It also helps greatly to confess venial sins.',
        resFaqQ5:'What if I forgot a sin?', resFaqA5:'If you forgot it unintentionally, the confession is still valid. Confess it in your next confession when you remember it.',
        resFaqQ6:'Do I have to give many details?', resFaqA6:'No. Speak clearly and simply. Say what is necessary for the sin to be understood, without unnecessary narration.',
        resFaqQ7:'Can the priest tell others what he heard?', resFaqA7:'No. What is heard in confession is completely protected by the sacramental seal.',
        resFaqQ8:'What if I do not know the act of contrition?', resFaqA8:'Do not worry. You can pray it with a familiar formula or express it in your own words, as long as you do so sincerely.',
        resFaqQ9:'What is contrition?', resFaqA9:'It is sorrow for having sinned and the sincere desire to return to God and turn away from sin.',
        resFaqQ10:'What is the purpose of amendment?', resFaqA10:'It is the real decision to strive to change and to avoid what leads you to sin.',
        resFaqQ11:'How often should one go to confession?', resFaqA11:'In addition to going when there is awareness of grave sin, it is highly recommended to confess frequently for spiritual growth.',
        resFaqQ12:'Can I receive Communion if I am aware of grave sin?', resFaqA12:'The right thing to do is to go first to the sacrament of reconciliation before approaching to receive Communion.',
        resFaqQ13:'What if I fall into the same sin again?', resFaqA13:'Get up and return to the Lord. Do not give up. Persevering in the struggle is also part of the path of conversion.',
        resFaqQ14:'Does penance replace forgiveness?', resFaqA14:'No. Forgiveness is given by God in absolution. Penance is a concrete response that helps cooperate with the grace received.',
